290
00:23:23,330 --> 00:23:25,600
-Han Yong-min!
-Han Yong-min!

291
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:34,810
("THE ROMANTICIST OF MUJI GETS
ELECTED THREE TIMES IN A ROW")

292
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:37,510
-Are you serious?
-Yes.

293
00:23:41,020 --> 00:23:42,920
-Sang-hwan is here.
-Congratulations.

294
00:23:43,550 --> 00:23:45,250
-Congratulations.
-Unbelievable.

295
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:46,920
Congratulations. Let's shake hands.

296
00:23:48,060 --> 00:23:50,190
-I'm so jealous.
-He's the son of our governor.

297
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:53,190
You must be so happy.

298
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:11,340
Do not be scared,
for I will always be with you.

299
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,010
Do not be surprised,

300
00:25:13,740 --> 00:25:15,580
for I will be your Almighty.

301
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:17,440
I will make you strong.

302
00:25:17,880 --> 00:25:19,650
I will help you.

303
00:25:19,810 --> 00:25:21,880
I will hold onto you

304
00:25:22,220 --> 00:25:23,650
with my right hand.

305
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,000
Yes.

306
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,700
It was all a message from Almighty.

307
00:25:58,850 --> 00:26:00,220
(Let's go to a karaoke room.)

308
00:26:01,290 --> 00:26:03,520
(How long has it been?)

309
00:26:05,530 --> 00:26:07,160
It's okay. Don't worry too much.

310
00:26:20,740 --> 00:26:24,450
How did you know I would be here?

311
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:27,380
Can I have

312
00:26:28,220 --> 00:26:29,880
Seok Dong-cheol's phone number?

313
00:26:33,690 --> 00:26:37,790
You won't be able to reach him
for a while.

314
00:26:40,390 --> 00:26:41,830
What do you mean?

315
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:44,700
Well, the thing is...

316
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:48,200
-How should I put this?
-Dong-cheol

317
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:51,970
went to a youth detention center.

318
00:26:53,110 --> 00:26:54,140
What?

319
00:26:54,740 --> 00:26:57,310
Why did he go there?

320
00:26:58,810 --> 00:26:59,950
Because of me.

321
00:27:01,420 --> 00:27:02,520
This all happened

322
00:27:04,590 --> 00:27:05,850
because of me.

323
00:27:26,370 --> 00:27:28,980
Hey, are you Seok Dong-cheol?

324
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:34,280
Why do you want to know?

325
00:27:36,320 --> 00:27:39,920
You're new here, so there should
be a welcoming ceremony.

326
00:27:49,830 --> 00:27:50,960
Take this.

327
00:27:51,830 --> 00:27:53,070
He came in first place

328
00:27:53,130 --> 00:27:56,100
at the national youth athletic
competition.

329
00:27:57,100 --> 00:27:58,840
So it's going to hurt a bit.

330
00:27:59,810 --> 00:28:01,070
Let me tell you something.

331
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:03,840
Someone gave me some pocket money,

332
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:06,310
and asked me to make you into
a disabled person.

333
00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:24,400
Who asked you to do that?

334
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:31,200
I'm home.

335
00:28:31,510 --> 00:28:33,440
Why did you come home so late?

336
00:28:35,180 --> 00:28:37,540
My homeroom teacher wanted
to talk to me.

337
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:39,910
Honey.

338
00:28:40,010 --> 00:28:42,550
Sang-mi's here. Let's go now.

339
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,150
Okay.

340
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:47,420
Where are we going?

341
00:28:47,490 --> 00:28:50,120
There's someplace
we need to go together.

342
00:28:50,760 --> 00:28:52,360
We're going to meet Sang-jin.

343
00:28:53,030 --> 00:28:55,530
Apparently, we'll be able to
meet him there.

344
00:28:56,730 --> 00:28:58,030
Dad, if we're going to

345
00:28:58,630 --> 00:29:00,230
that place we went last time,
I don't want to go.

346
00:29:00,300 --> 00:29:02,600
You know that Mom's condition
became worse after that day.

347
00:29:03,070 --> 00:29:05,710
We're not going there today.

348
00:29:07,010 --> 00:29:08,080
Then where are we going?

349
00:29:08,210 --> 00:29:09,340
We're going to Guseonwon.

350
00:29:10,710 --> 00:29:11,910
Guseonwon?

351
00:29:15,950 --> 00:29:16,950
Sang-mi.

352
00:29:17,250 --> 00:29:19,550
I finally get it now.

353
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:21,820
The reason why we came to this
neighborhood.

354
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:23,690
The reason why Sang-jin
had to die like that.

355
00:29:24,190 --> 00:29:25,760
The reason why your mom's
suffering like this.

356
00:29:26,190 --> 00:29:28,760
It was all a message that
our Almighty was trying to send to us.

357
00:29:30,430 --> 00:29:32,370
Dad, what are you talking about?

358
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:37,070
We became the chosen ones
by our Almighty.

359
00:29:37,140 --> 00:29:39,370
Stop saying weird stuff!

360
00:29:39,970 --> 00:29:41,610
Let's not do this.

361
00:29:41,910 --> 00:29:44,810
Let's just take Mom to a big
hospital in Seoul.

362
00:29:47,380 --> 00:29:48,480
Sang-mi.

363
00:29:49,150 --> 00:29:53,520
Guseonwon is the only place
that can heal your mother.

364
00:29:54,590 --> 00:29:58,330
Let's go there and
let the Spiritual Father pray for us.

365
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:03,130
You're lying.

366
00:30:07,230 --> 00:30:08,300
What?

367
00:30:08,370 --> 00:30:09,740
Stop lying.

368
00:30:11,170 --> 00:30:12,870
What do you mean?

369
00:30:17,410 --> 00:30:19,350
You're doing this
because of that woman.

370
00:30:19,680 --> 00:30:20,810
Sang-mi.

371
00:30:21,010 --> 00:30:24,450
I saw you with her earlier.

372
00:30:24,750 --> 00:30:26,350
I'm scared.

373
00:30:26,490 --> 00:30:28,820
Those people give me the creeps.

374
00:30:29,690 --> 00:30:32,690
Sang-mi, don't say that.

375
00:30:33,060 --> 00:30:37,930
They're special messengers
who are here to save us.

376
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:43,670
Dad.

377
00:30:45,070 --> 00:30:46,640
Why on earth
are you being like this?

378
00:30:54,550 --> 00:30:57,420
Sang-mi, I'm really

379
00:30:58,820 --> 00:31:01,360
doing this for you and your mom.

380
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:05,060
So please trust me.

381
00:31:06,030 --> 00:31:07,090
Just once more.

382
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:11,370
Trust me just once more. Please?

383
00:31:16,970 --> 00:31:18,000
Please?

384
00:31:19,140 --> 00:31:20,140
Dad.

385
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:28,520
Let's go see Sang-jin.

386
00:32:00,310 --> 00:32:07,320
(MEET ALMIGHTY AT GUSEONWON)

387
00:32:09,790 --> 00:32:11,160
-Hello.
-Hello.

388
00:32:13,730 --> 00:32:15,330
-It's okay. Don't worry.
-Be careful.

389
00:32:20,970 --> 00:32:22,000
Watch the steps.

390
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:25,270
Here's a can of soda.

391
00:32:26,140 --> 00:32:27,910
Jeong-gu likes soda.

392
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:33,250
My gosh, what's gotten into you, Jeong-gu?

393
00:32:33,310 --> 00:32:34,680
You're giving it to her?

394
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,020
Here at Guseonwon, we call him Angel.

395
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:39,250
He loves soda so much

396
00:32:39,490 --> 00:32:41,920
that he never offers it to anyone
except for his grandmother.

397
00:32:42,060 --> 00:32:44,990
Gosh, Jeong-gu. You sure are a boy.

398
00:32:45,060 --> 00:32:46,360
You like pretty girls too, don't you?

399
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:51,900
Sang-jin. Sang-jin...

400
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,200
What?

401
00:32:53,370 --> 00:32:54,500
Sang-jin.

402
00:32:54,870 --> 00:32:56,440
-Right, Sang-jin.
-Oh, right.

403
00:32:56,500 --> 00:32:58,810
Spiritual Father is waiting for you.
Let's go.

404
00:32:58,870 --> 00:33:00,510
-Okay.
-Sang-jin.

405
00:33:14,450 --> 00:33:19,460
(Hide carefully,
I can see strands of your hair)

406
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:27,830
(Hide carefully,
I can see strands of your hair)

407
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:35,680
(Hide carefully,
I can see strands of your hair)

408
00:33:44,450 --> 00:33:45,720
Found you.

409
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:28,030
(2017, 3 YEARS LATER)

410
00:34:56,290 --> 00:34:57,320
Excuse me.

411
00:34:58,790 --> 00:35:00,260
You have such a pure soul.

412
00:35:00,330 --> 00:35:02,460
Your face tells us that you were
born with so much good fortune.

413
00:35:02,530 --> 00:35:05,200
Your ancestors must've done
a lot of good deeds.

414
00:35:05,370 --> 00:35:08,300
Please allow us to share a few words
of wisdom over a cup of tea.

415
00:35:10,470 --> 00:35:12,570
Wait, sir. It won't take long.

416
00:35:13,410 --> 00:35:15,310
A motorcycle, which was driving
along a shoulder

417
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:17,210
between a three-lane road
and sidewalk,

418
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:20,480
bumped into a taxi that was pulled
over as its door opened suddenly.

419
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:25,250
After the accident, the driver
sued the private taxi association,

420
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:27,520
and court ruled that the
association is responsible

421
00:35:27,590 --> 00:35:29,120
for 70 percent
of the total damages,

422
00:35:29,190 --> 00:35:32,160
and the driver of the motorcycle
for 30 percent.

423
00:35:32,230 --> 00:35:36,430
The verdict was certainly in favor
of the driver of the motorcycle.

424
00:35:36,530 --> 00:35:40,430
Do any of you think
that the verdict is problematic?

425
00:35:42,500 --> 00:35:44,140
Yes, you in the red blouse.

426
00:35:44,200 --> 00:35:46,970
In cities, you see motorcycles
not staying within lanes,

427
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:49,940
and they often drive
in between cars.

428
00:35:50,010 --> 00:35:52,850
Many drivers have experienced
dangerous situations.

429
00:35:53,210 --> 00:35:54,650
Hence, I think that the verdict

430
00:35:54,710 --> 00:35:57,820
might actually encourage motorcycle
drivers to drive on shoulders.

431
00:35:57,880 --> 00:36:00,190
That's where I think problems
can arise.

432
00:36:00,520 --> 00:36:02,160
Right, I see.

433
00:36:02,790 --> 00:36:04,620
Does anyone have a different opinion?

434
00:36:08,190 --> 00:36:09,230
Yes, you over there.

435
00:36:11,530 --> 00:36:13,100
As for this case,

436
00:36:13,170 --> 00:36:15,740
court deemed the taxi driver
more responsible for the accident,

437
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,900
but I don't think the verdict was wrong.

438
00:36:18,710 --> 00:36:21,980
In my opinion, the bigger
problem is that

439
00:36:22,210 --> 00:36:24,740
the customer who opened the door
wasn't considered a defendant.

440
00:36:25,450 --> 00:36:27,880
The driver of the motorcycle
just sued the association.

441
00:36:28,110 --> 00:36:30,480
Had the customer of the taxi
been one of the defendants,

442
00:36:30,550 --> 00:36:32,750
both the customer
and the association

443
00:36:32,820 --> 00:36:35,290
would've been held responsible
for the damages.

444
00:36:35,560 --> 00:36:38,220
If that was the case, the association

445
00:36:38,290 --> 00:36:41,060
might decide to sue
the customer as well later on.

446
00:36:49,140 --> 00:36:52,210
Hey, Sang-hwan. You have to come
to the end-of-semester party, okay?

447
00:36:53,740 --> 00:36:54,870
Hey, wait.

448
00:36:55,610 --> 00:36:59,210
The seniors said everyone
has to be there.

449
00:37:01,210 --> 00:37:02,220
You'll come, right?

450
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,650
-Cheers.
-Cheers. Nice to meet you all.

451
00:37:09,390 --> 00:37:10,420
Hey, you.

452
00:37:11,060 --> 00:37:13,260
Why aren't you drinking?

453
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:17,430
I'm a lightweight.

454
00:37:19,000 --> 00:37:20,030
What?

455
00:37:21,330 --> 00:37:23,040
I can't drink much.

456
00:37:41,220 --> 00:37:42,390
Drink up.

457
00:37:46,630 --> 00:37:47,660
(Eat.)

458
00:37:48,390 --> 00:37:51,200
Hey, I said eat your lunch!

459
00:37:52,700 --> 00:37:54,970
Drink up, you jerk!

460
00:37:57,170 --> 00:37:58,200
(Please help me.)

461
00:37:59,640 --> 00:38:02,380
Please help my brother.

462
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:08,720
You said you'll take care of it
on your own.

463
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:25,830
Okay, I will.

464
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:32,170
Hey, don't drink that.

465
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:38,410
Who would want to drink your saliva?
It's disgusting.

466
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:40,650
And according to Article 324
of the Criminal Code,

467
00:38:40,710 --> 00:38:41,880
you're committing coercion now.

468
00:38:41,950 --> 00:38:42,950
What?

469
00:38:43,420 --> 00:38:44,880
Those who exercise violence
or use threats

470
00:38:44,950 --> 00:38:48,120
to obstruct someone's rights
or force someone to do something

471
00:38:49,720 --> 00:38:51,220
can be sentenced to
up to five years in prison

472
00:38:51,290 --> 00:38:52,990
or amerced up to 30 million won.

473
00:38:55,530 --> 00:38:58,530
Gosh, who is this lunatic?

474
00:38:58,800 --> 00:39:01,670
Hey, where's the representative
for the first year students?

475
00:39:01,730 --> 00:39:03,240
Yes, I'm here.

476
00:39:03,870 --> 00:39:05,170
-Are you the representative?
-Yes.

477
00:39:06,070 --> 00:39:08,070
This is all because you haven't
been behaving yourself.

478
00:39:08,510 --> 00:39:10,940
That's why those under you
can act up like that.

479
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:14,110
Do you want to be charged
with assault too?

480
00:39:14,810 --> 00:39:15,750
Let go.

481
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,320
Hey, what do you think
you're doing now?

482
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:19,190
Are you out of your mind?
Let go of his hand!

483
00:39:22,290 --> 00:39:23,560
Are you all right?

484
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:28,760
Hey!

485
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,500
If this idiot isn't going to drink it,

486
00:39:36,070 --> 00:39:39,210
you'll have to drink it yourself
before you go. Got it?

487
00:39:43,540 --> 00:39:45,210
My goodness.

488
00:39:45,580 --> 00:39:49,350
Sang-hwan, how did you suppress
yourself in all these years?

489
00:39:50,480 --> 00:39:53,220
What? Is this idiot from the countryside?

490
00:40:01,090 --> 00:40:04,060
All right, then. This is self-defense.

491
00:40:05,060 --> 00:40:06,900
-My gosh!
-Gosh!

492
00:40:09,170 --> 00:40:10,300
You little...

493
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:32,330
Quit making lame attempts,
and just come at me all at once.

494
00:40:45,670 --> 00:40:47,310
What do you plan on doing
once you get out?

495
00:40:48,170 --> 00:40:49,410
I'll have to work hard

496
00:40:50,010 --> 00:40:51,540
and make a living.

497
00:40:52,580 --> 00:40:54,780
Now that you've gotten neat haircut,

498
00:40:55,380 --> 00:40:57,050
you should start over and
become a new man.

499
00:41:06,660 --> 00:41:08,590
Move it slowly. Move it slowly.

500
00:41:16,740 --> 00:41:18,400
Move aside a bit.

501
00:41:18,640 --> 00:41:21,710
That's perfect. Move it down slowly.

502
00:41:22,180 --> 00:41:23,940
That's right. That's perfect.

503
00:41:24,440 --> 00:41:25,610
Be careful.

504
00:41:25,910 --> 00:41:28,150
Move slowly. Slowly, please.

505
00:41:28,210 --> 00:41:30,620
Move it down slowly. That's perfect.

506
00:41:46,870 --> 00:41:48,230
Welcome, Senator Park.

507
00:41:48,300 --> 00:41:51,470
I haven't come in such a long time.
Forgive me.

508
00:41:52,310 --> 00:41:53,510
Don't be sorry.

509
00:41:53,710 --> 00:41:56,640
You've become the highest member
of your party. I'm sure you're busy.

510
00:41:57,780 --> 00:42:01,310
Your father is in good hands.
There's no need to worry.

511
00:42:02,720 --> 00:42:03,820
Dad.

512
00:42:04,680 --> 00:42:05,990
I've come to see you.

513
00:42:06,490 --> 00:42:08,250
Aren't you my son's friend?

514
00:42:09,820 --> 00:42:12,030
I'm your son, Yeong-cheol.

515
00:42:18,630 --> 00:42:22,470
In order to see you more often,

516
00:42:22,900 --> 00:42:24,640
I should make more visits.

517
00:42:25,470 --> 00:42:27,510
Would you like to have a meal
with me some time?

518
00:42:27,570 --> 00:42:29,110
How is your health, Senator?

519
00:42:32,150 --> 00:42:34,480
Ever since I've started drinking
the Living Water you gave me,

520
00:42:34,550 --> 00:42:36,750
I've been able to sleep well at night.

521
00:42:39,590 --> 00:42:44,260
That proves how much Almighty
loves you, Senator.

522
00:42:44,820 --> 00:42:46,590
It's Almighty's blessing, isn't it?

523
00:42:47,730 --> 00:42:49,600
Senator, thanks to you,

524
00:42:49,730 --> 00:42:51,500
Muji has developed greatly.

525
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:54,330
It's all thanks to you, Spiritual Father.

526
00:43:14,890 --> 00:43:16,620
(MUJI DISTRICT OFFICE, WITHDRAW
PERMISSION TO CONSTRUCT SANITARIUM)

527
00:43:16,690 --> 00:43:17,890
(DISTRICT OFFICE SHOULD APOLOGIZE
FOR CAJOLING MUJI RESIDENTS)

528
00:43:21,860 --> 00:43:22,860
Hey.

529
00:43:23,630 --> 00:43:25,400
You're the governor's son, aren't you?

530
00:43:26,330 --> 00:43:27,670
You must've mistaken me for
someone else.

531
00:43:29,570 --> 00:43:30,670
Come see me some time.

532
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:34,710
I'll give you a good time. All right?

533
00:43:44,380 --> 00:43:47,890
Isn't that Sang-hwan?
I haven't seen him in a long time.

534
00:43:48,390 --> 00:43:50,260
Gosh. He sure is good-looking.

535
00:44:41,810 --> 00:44:44,510
We're up here. Sang-hwan.
Sang-hwan.

536
00:44:44,580 --> 00:44:45,650
You're here.

537
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:47,250
Gosh.

538
00:44:47,310 --> 00:44:49,050
-We got you. We got you.
-Gosh.

539
00:44:49,550 --> 00:44:50,650
You guys wait right there.

540
00:44:52,650 --> 00:44:56,020
Hey! I got you! Die!

541
00:44:57,420 --> 00:44:59,490
Hey. Why did you shoot water at me?

542
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:02,090
Welcome, Sang-hwan.

543
00:45:02,860 --> 00:45:03,900
How have you guys been?

544
00:45:05,830 --> 00:45:07,100
Do you still do that show?

545
00:45:07,170 --> 00:45:09,300
Of course. You won't believe
how many viewers I have.

546
00:45:10,100 --> 00:45:11,140
Shut your mouth.

547
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:12,640
How long has it been since you
were here?

548
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:14,170
Hasn't it been almost three years?

549
00:45:14,340 --> 00:45:15,540
It's been about three years.

550
00:45:16,210 --> 00:45:18,710
Anyway, how did you guys know I was here?

551
00:45:18,910 --> 00:45:21,550
Of course the source of all
information in Muji,

552
00:45:21,610 --> 00:45:24,680
Pil-su, told us. He said he saw you
at the terminal.

553
00:45:25,450 --> 00:45:27,290
This town is way too small.

554
00:45:29,460 --> 00:45:31,390
Gosh. When you come here,

555
00:45:31,460 --> 00:45:36,330
you should bring along some
girls from Seoul.

556
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,730
You should know better.

557
00:45:39,430 --> 00:45:40,470
Gosh.

558
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:42,100
Are you ignoring me?

559
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:43,670
That's exactly what I'm doing.

560
00:45:45,770 --> 00:45:48,340
Don't move. Attention, at ease,
attention, at ease. Face down.

561
00:45:48,410 --> 00:45:50,440
Face down. Put your head
on the floor.

562
00:45:50,510 --> 00:45:52,880
-I won't let you ignore me.
-Cut it out.

563
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:55,680
Gosh. You guys haven't changed a bit.

564
00:45:56,180 --> 00:45:57,250
Do as I say.

565
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:58,880
-Give that back.
-Don't move.

566
00:46:05,490 --> 00:46:08,100
They shouldn't be making noises.

567
00:46:09,800 --> 00:46:11,000
They'll get in trouble.

568
00:46:16,600 --> 00:46:18,770
This is soda. I like it.

569
00:46:22,040 --> 00:46:23,110
What was that?

570
00:46:24,410 --> 00:46:25,850
Are we playing hide-and-seek?

571
00:46:27,150 --> 00:46:31,450
(Hide carefully,
I can see strands of your hair)

572
00:46:48,130 --> 00:46:49,240
Where are you?

573
00:46:51,570 --> 00:46:54,240
There you are. I found you.

574
00:47:09,460 --> 00:47:11,360
(Please stop. Stop it.)

575
00:47:12,560 --> 00:47:14,390
(Please stop. Help me.)

576
00:47:15,830 --> 00:47:18,260
(SONG JI-EUN)

577
00:47:28,010 --> 00:47:29,340
They're fighting.

578
00:47:29,940 --> 00:47:32,880
You shouldn't fight. It's not right.

579
00:47:39,950 --> 00:47:41,090
It's you.

580
00:47:41,350 --> 00:47:44,220
It's you again. Mr. Jo.

581
00:47:44,620 --> 00:47:46,490
Jeong-gu likes soda.

582
00:47:50,430 --> 00:47:53,230
Mister, give me soda.

583
00:47:53,600 --> 00:47:55,400
Jeong-gu likes soda.

584
00:48:48,250 --> 00:48:49,960
Sang-mi.

585
00:48:52,090 --> 00:48:56,760
You showed us everything last time.
Don't act shy.

586
00:48:56,830 --> 00:48:58,130
This fool peed in his pants.

587
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:00,570
Sang-mi.

588
00:49:04,740 --> 00:49:05,870
Jeong-gu.

589
00:49:08,940 --> 00:49:10,410
What do you think you're doing?

590
00:49:15,380 --> 00:49:16,450
It's not what you think.

591
00:49:16,750 --> 00:49:18,820
Jeong-gu was caught stealing money.

592
00:49:18,880 --> 00:49:20,490
That's nonsense.

593
00:49:20,820 --> 00:49:22,960
You know perfectly well he's not
the type that would do such a thing.

594
00:49:24,260 --> 00:49:26,460
How would you know?
You never know.

595
00:49:26,730 --> 00:49:28,630
He might be putting up an act right now.

596
00:49:29,330 --> 00:49:30,760
If you beat him one more time,

597
00:49:32,400 --> 00:49:35,470
I'm really going to report you
to the police.

598
00:49:36,270 --> 00:49:37,340
Sang-mi.

599
00:49:38,400 --> 00:49:40,070
What are you saying right now?

600
00:49:40,410 --> 00:49:42,840
Someone might mistakenly think
that I beat him often.

601
00:49:46,380 --> 00:49:48,010
Don't think I'm stupid.

602
00:49:53,020 --> 00:49:56,520
There seems to be a big
misunderstanding here.

603
00:49:56,590 --> 00:49:57,890
I didn't beat him.

604
00:49:58,260 --> 00:50:02,090
I just punished him to prevent
this from happening again.

605
00:50:02,160 --> 00:50:06,600
Jeong-gu is the person I care for
the most in Guseonwon.

606
00:50:07,130 --> 00:50:08,770
Why would I ever hit him
without having a good reason?

607
00:50:10,500 --> 00:50:11,640
Don't you agree, Jeong-gu?

608
00:50:13,810 --> 00:50:17,380
Jeong-gu, you must be trying
to make her feel sorry for you

609
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:19,480
because she's holding you
in her arms.

610
00:50:20,650 --> 00:50:21,650
Let's go.

611
00:50:22,180 --> 00:50:23,620
Let's go and have you get changed.

612
00:50:27,090 --> 00:50:28,690
Be careful.

613
00:50:37,600 --> 00:50:38,630
Sang-mi.

614
00:50:41,370 --> 00:50:43,100
Everything that happens in Guseonwon

615
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:46,440
needs to be kept and dealt with
in Guseonwon. You know that, right?

616
00:50:49,980 --> 00:50:51,080
Bye, Jeong-gu.

617
00:51:43,700 --> 00:51:45,360
Jeong-gu's sick.

618
00:51:45,430 --> 00:51:47,200
We need to take him to the
hospital right now.

619
00:51:49,340 --> 00:51:50,470
Our wishes will be fulfilled.

620
00:51:50,740 --> 00:51:52,240
My goodness, Sang-mi.

621
00:51:52,970 --> 00:51:54,940
Don't you know
that we are in a silent period?

622
00:51:55,210 --> 00:51:56,680
You did that to him.

623
00:51:59,310 --> 00:52:01,150
Sang-mi, stop being so rude.

624
00:52:01,410 --> 00:52:04,520
How many times must I tell you to
call him Apostle Jo?

625
00:52:04,720 --> 00:52:07,690
He's right, Sang-mi.
Instead of going to the hospital,

626
00:52:08,520 --> 00:52:11,020
he can just drink Living Water
to get better.

627
00:52:11,660 --> 00:52:12,730
Our wishes will be fulfilled.

628
00:52:13,690 --> 00:52:14,830
Dad.

629
00:52:19,030 --> 00:52:20,030
Sang-mi.

630
00:52:20,400 --> 00:52:23,800
The Spiritual Father's
Living Water can cure anyone.

631
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:26,270
He's just suffering from a bad cold,
so just a drop of Living Water

632
00:52:26,340 --> 00:52:28,370
will make him get better in no time.
Okay?

633
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:29,580
He's right, Sang-mi.

634
00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:31,980
Let's cure him with our faith.

635
00:52:35,180 --> 00:52:38,980
Do you guys seriously believe in that?

636
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:41,120
Do you really think

637
00:52:42,350 --> 00:52:44,290
that water can work miracles?

638
00:52:44,360 --> 00:52:47,290
Sang-mi, how dare you say such
evil things?

639
00:52:47,530 --> 00:52:48,560
I want you to repent on
what you just said.

640
00:52:48,630 --> 00:52:49,660
Dad!

641
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:52,230
Please wake up and
come to your senses.

642
00:52:52,530 --> 00:52:55,770
That water won't help Jeong-gu.
He needs to go to the hospital.

643
00:52:56,740 --> 00:53:00,070
Until when are you going to
live your life like this?

644
00:53:00,140 --> 00:53:01,310
Three years have passed.

645
00:53:01,370 --> 00:53:02,640
Every year, I always wished that
we'd get out of here.

646
00:53:02,710 --> 00:53:04,040
But it's been three years already.

647
00:53:06,480 --> 00:53:07,680
Look at Mom.

648
00:53:09,280 --> 00:53:12,020
How can you call this a place of
salvation and miracles?

649
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:25,330
Sang... Sang-mi.

650
00:53:25,730 --> 00:53:27,670
I was just--

651
00:53:27,730 --> 00:53:28,800
You're crazy.

652
00:53:33,940 --> 00:53:35,810
Staying here like this

653
00:53:37,510 --> 00:53:39,010
is just crazy.

654
00:53:42,580 --> 00:53:44,780
You guys are all crazy too.

655
00:53:45,650 --> 00:53:46,720
Salvation?

656
00:53:48,020 --> 00:53:49,090
Eternal life?

657
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:52,690
Do you really think you can
get that from living here?

658
00:53:53,060 --> 00:53:56,430
Please get back to your senses.

659
00:53:57,160 --> 00:53:58,160
Sang-mi.

660
00:53:58,930 --> 00:54:00,430
I can't take this anymore.

661
00:54:00,830 --> 00:54:03,770
Apostle Jo, please take her to
the prayer room.

662
00:54:06,310 --> 00:54:07,470
Our wishes will be fulfilled.

663
00:54:09,840 --> 00:54:11,540
Let's go pray, Sang-mi.

664
00:54:11,740 --> 00:54:13,080
-Let me go.
-Let's go pray.

665
00:54:13,150 --> 00:54:14,280
I said, let me go!

666
00:54:14,410 --> 00:54:15,710
Call him out.

667
00:54:25,420 --> 00:54:27,460
If someone's sick,

668
00:54:28,230 --> 00:54:30,330
that person should go to the hospital.

669
00:54:31,130 --> 00:54:32,560
Without faith,

670
00:54:33,330 --> 00:54:36,270
this liquid right here is just
a bottle of plain water,

671
00:54:37,170 --> 00:54:38,500
just like what Sang-mi said.

672
00:54:39,070 --> 00:54:41,870
If you pretend to believe only
because you're scared about...

673
00:54:41,940 --> 00:54:43,440
what the others might think of you,

674
00:54:43,940 --> 00:54:46,350
that would be the biggest sin
you could ever commit.

675
00:55:00,290 --> 00:55:01,760
I'm sure you think

676
00:55:02,690 --> 00:55:05,430
everything here is fake.

677
00:55:07,100 --> 00:55:10,840
But you'll soon realize that

678
00:55:12,640 --> 00:55:14,210
everything here is real.

679
00:55:15,840 --> 00:55:17,080
The outside world

680
00:55:19,310 --> 00:55:20,780
is what's fake.

681
00:56:29,550 --> 00:56:31,050
What are you saying to him?

682
00:56:33,620 --> 00:56:36,260
Sang-mi, you're so sensitive.

683
00:56:36,960 --> 00:56:39,190
I think of Jeong-gu
as my own family.

684
00:56:39,260 --> 00:56:42,830
Is it a bad thing to ask
if he's doing okay?

685
00:56:46,500 --> 00:56:48,570
I think Jeong-gu can go home now.

686
00:56:50,640 --> 00:56:51,740
Excuse me.

687
00:56:53,640 --> 00:56:54,840
What do you mean he can go home?

688
00:56:58,940 --> 00:57:02,180
I'm not sick.

689
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:06,590
I miss my grandmother.

690
00:57:06,650 --> 00:57:07,920
Okay, let's go.

691
00:57:22,570 --> 00:57:24,470
We're almost out of gas.

692
00:57:27,270 --> 00:57:30,080
Let's put in some gas
at that gas station.

693
00:57:34,980 --> 00:57:37,250
Sang-mi, I'm going to go take a leak.

694
00:57:42,690 --> 00:57:43,720
My gosh.

695
00:57:54,500 --> 00:57:55,870
Jeong-gu, are you cold?

696
00:57:57,870 --> 00:57:59,740
I'm scared.

697
00:58:01,810 --> 00:58:02,870
Are you scared?

698
00:58:05,010 --> 00:58:06,880
I'm scared of him.

699
00:58:07,750 --> 00:58:09,250
He hit me.

700
00:58:10,050 --> 00:58:12,020
You shouldn't swear.

701
00:58:12,480 --> 00:58:15,590
That lady kept saying that it hurt.

702
00:58:16,150 --> 00:58:18,290
But he kept hitting her.

703
00:58:20,060 --> 00:58:23,330
She kept telling him to stop.

704
00:58:30,600 --> 00:58:33,640
Jeong-gu, what do you mean?

705
00:58:34,740 --> 00:58:36,240
Did he also hit

706
00:58:37,210 --> 00:58:38,980
other people?

707
00:58:39,680 --> 00:58:41,750
You're a bad person
if you hit someone.

708
00:58:41,810 --> 00:58:44,420
So he's a bad person.

709
00:58:44,580 --> 00:58:46,350
"I'm going to kill you if you
say anything."

710
00:58:46,890 --> 00:58:50,690
"I'm going to kill you
and your grandmother."

711
00:59:27,690 --> 00:59:28,960
Get off me.

712
00:59:58,160 --> 01:00:01,660
Here's that soda you like so much,
Jeong-gu.

713
01:00:02,460 --> 01:00:06,930
I'm giving it to you since you were
such a good boy.

714
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:09,100
Aren't you happy?

715
01:00:10,800 --> 01:00:11,940
It's soda.

716
01:00:14,410 --> 01:00:16,410
I like soda.

717
01:00:21,180 --> 01:00:24,280
That phone doesn't even work.

718
01:00:24,520 --> 01:00:26,990
Why are you holding on to it so tightly?

719
01:00:28,550 --> 01:00:29,590
Tell me.

720
01:00:49,570 --> 01:00:52,780
Gosh. Drive smoothly, will you?

721
01:00:53,310 --> 01:00:56,110
We have a patient in the car.
Don't pass speed bumps so quickly.

722
01:00:57,420 --> 01:01:00,520
Speed bumps mean you should
slow down, don't they?

723
01:02:14,430 --> 01:02:17,100
(SAVE ME)

724
01:02:17,260 --> 01:02:19,530
Almighty, please help me.

725
01:02:21,730 --> 01:02:22,970
Indeed.

726
01:02:23,130 --> 01:02:26,370
Our Spiritual Father will save you.
He is eternal.

727
01:02:26,570 --> 01:02:28,970
Those who believe in him will
live after death.

728
01:02:29,040 --> 01:02:30,640
You will go on living forever.

729
01:02:33,350 --> 01:02:34,710
Drink plenty of water.
